result.execSummary:
The defendant Holden S Monte was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Holden S Monte in court.  Attorney Sherman appears telephonically. Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:15 PM. State - has complied with victim notification requirements with no response - plead to #1 as previously amended, joint recommendation of a fine of $500 plus costs, #2 - DRI. Sherman and Monte agree. Court goes thru verbal collaquey with the defendant regarding having his attorney appearing telephonically today's proceedings. Monte provides court with plea questionnaire. Court dismisses and reads in count #2. Court amends count #1 to misd battery contrary to 940.19(1) - delete repeater and hate crime - reads new charge and penalty. Sherman advises the defendant to plead NC to amended count #1. State has no objections to pleading NC. Court has concerns taking the plea at this point with the attorney appearing telephonically and the defendant being confused. Recess to give Monte a chance to talk to Sherman (1:20 PM). Recalled at 1:44 PM, same appearances. Sherman has spoken with the defendant and defendants will plead NC to amended count #1. Monte agrees and understands today's proceedings. Monte pleads NC to amended count #1. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation. Sherman - follow joint recommendation. Monte makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - $500 fine plus costs totalling $1083.00 - take bond posted - remainder due 60 days/CO, right to appeal to be filed within the next 10 days, adjourned.
